               <p>SARAH STAINES. I lost these loaves, on Saturday, the 13th of March; I locked my door at about twelve and one, and left the key in; I went into the washhouse for a moment, and when I returned, the door was opened, and the loaves were gone. The prisoner was brought back with the loaves.</p>

               <p>
            
